      "id": "PopularPost123798",
      "post_content": "The akki seemed to have a bit of a land-hate flavour given to them - see this, [Akki Avalanchers](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Akki Avalanchers), [Akki Raider](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Akki Raider) and the ever-cool [Zo-Zu the Punisher](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Zo-Zu the Punisher). I wonder if this is intended to reflect something about the actual Japanese akki mythology?\n  \n   \nFlavour aside, this is quite similar to [Tremble](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tremble) - comparing the two, the upside to this guy is that he could attack for you a couple of times, but the downside is that you might not be able to pop him when you really want to. He makes for an interesting in-block combo with the aforementioned Raider, and while this amounts to an underwhelming +2/+0 ueot in a duel, it could get much stronger in a multiplayer situation. ",
      "posted_by": "Leshrac_Nightwalker",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost123798\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\">The akki seemed to have a bit of a land-hate flavour given to them - see this, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Akki Avalanchers\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Akki Avalanchers\">Akki Avalanchers</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Akki Raider\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Akki Raider\">Akki Raider</a> and the ever-cool <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Zo-Zu the Punisher\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Zo-Zu the Punisher\">Zo-Zu the Punisher</a>.  I wonder if this is intended to reflect something about the actual Japanese akki mythology?  \r<br/> <br/>Flavour aside, this is quite similar to <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Tremble\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tremble\">Tremble</a> - comparing the two, the upside to this guy is that he could attack for you a couple of times, but the downside is that you might not be able to pop him when you really want to.  He makes for an interesting in-block combo with the aforementioned Raider, and while this amounts to an underwhelming +2/+0 ueot in a duel, it could get much stronger in a multiplayer situation.  </span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '123798'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n    